      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Include some mechanism in your app, such as a Restore Purchases button, to let users restore their in-app purchases. In rare cases when a user suspects the app isn’t showing all the transactions, call ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.storekit/documentation/StoreKit/AppStore/sync()",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ". By calling ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.storekit/documentation/StoreKit/AppStore/sync()",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ", you force the app to obtain transaction information and subscription status from the App Store.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "Calling ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.storekit/documentation/StoreKit/AppStore/sync()",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "type": "reference"
                },
                {
                  "text": "displays a system prompt that asks users to authenticate with their App Store credentials. Call this function only in response to an explicit user action, like tapping or clicking a button.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Important",
          "style": "important",
          "type": "aside"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "In regular operations, there’s no need to call ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.storekit/documentation/StoreKit/AppStore/sync()",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ". StoreKit automatically keeps up to date transaction information and subscription status available to your app. When users reinstall your app or download it on a new device, the app automatically has all transactions available to it upon initial launch. There’s no need for users to ask your app to restore transactions — your app can immediately get the current entitlements using ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.storekit/documentation/StoreKit/Transaction/currentEntitlements",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " and transaction history using ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.storekit/documentation/StoreKit/Transaction/all",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ". For more information about transactions, see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.storekit/documentation/StoreKit/Transaction",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
